Got it! Here is a list of the Nobel Laureates in Literature from 2010 to 2015, along with their most famous works:

2010: Mario Vargas Llosa, a Peruvian author, is best known for his novels, such as *The Time of the Hero* (1963), *Conversation in the Cathedral* (1969), and *The Feast of the Goat* (2000). He has also written several other notable works, including *The City and the Dogs* and *Aunt Julia and the Scriptwriter*.

2011: Tomas Tranströmer, a Swedish poet and psychologist, is renowned for his collections of poems, including *17 Poems* (1954), *The Half-Finished Heaven* (1962), and *Windows and Stones* (1966). Some of his other notable works are *The Sorrow Gondola* and *For the Living and the Dead*.

2012: Mo Yan, a Chinese author, is known for his novels, such as *Red Sorghum* (1986), *The Garlic Ballads* (1988), and *Big Breasts & Wide Hips* (1996). His other famous works include *The Republic of Wine*, *Frog*, and *Life and Death Are Wearing Me Out*.

2013: Alice Munro, a Canadian short story writer, is celebrated for her collection of short stories *The Moons of Jupiter* (1982), *Friend of My Youth* (1990), and *The Love of a Good Woman* (1998). Some of her other notable works are *Dance of the Happy Shades*, *The Progress of Love*, and *Hateship, Friendship, Courtship, Loveship, Marriage*.

2014: Patrick Modiano, a French novelist, is best remembered for his novels *Rue des Boutiques Obscures* (1978), *After the Night*, and *The Search Warrant* (1997). He has also written many other notable works, including *Missing Person* and *Dora Bruder*.

2015: Svetlana Alexievich, a Belarusian journalist and non-fiction writer, is renowned for her books *Voices from Chernobyl: The Oral History of a Nuclear Disaster* (1997), *Zinky Boys: Soviet Voices from the Afghanistan War* (1990), and *Second-Hand Time: The Last of the Soviets* (2013). Her other notable works include *The Unwomanly Face of War*.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.
